text.tspan: Child mortality vs share of children immunized against diphtheria, pertussis,
On the x-axis: Share of children (12-23 months) that are immunized against diphtheria, pertussis, and typhoid (DPT). On the
y-axis: Number of children per 1,000 live births who die before reaching the age of 5.
Source: Immunization against DPT – World Bank (WDI) (2016), Child Mortality Estimates - CME Info (2016)
